13/07/552964_462316357177575_2038693124_n.jpg 900w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/552964_462316357177575_2038693124_n-150x150.jpg 150w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/552964_462316357177575_2038693124_n-300x300.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a>  <a href="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/556179_304669216275624_1259439273_n.jpg" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone  wp-image-617" alt="556179_304669216275624_1259439273_n" src="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/556179_304669216275624_1259439273_n.jpg" width="247" height="302" /></a><a href="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/2566172.jpg" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone  wp-image-618" alt="2566172" src="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/2566172.jpg" width="554" height="392" srcset="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/2566172.jpg 900w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/2566172-300x211.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 554px) 100vw, 554px" /></a>Aren&#8217;t those lovely?  You can find more from this photographer at his<a href="http://www.photodom.com/member/aikijohn" target="_blank"> photodom.com</a> site or his <a href="https://www.facebook.com/evgeny.kornienko" target="_blank">Facebook</a>.  I&#8217;d love to tell you something about this artist, but &#8230; well, I can&#8217;t read Russian and I don&#8217;t trust Google Translate.  Still, you know what they say about pictures speaking 1000 words and all.</p>
<p>Are you an artist/photographer/sculptor who loves Steampunk as much as I do?   Would you like to see your work featured on this blog?  Or, do you know of someone else who’s work you adore?  Please leave a comment on this post with a link or two!   I’ll happily feature anything that I think will fit the style of my blog.  And even if I don’t feature it, please please leave your info in a comment anyway!  More art is always better than less.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
